data.title: Richie Holle
data.text:
Bio

Previous College: Attended Mount St. Mary's University.

As a Graduate (Tampa, 2021): Appeared in eleven games... SSC Commissioner's Honor Roll... Scored five goals total, including two in the season finale against Lynn (05/08)... Had three points in the NCAA tournament (2G, 1A): one goal and an assist against Mount Olive (05/14) and one goal against Lenoir-Rhyne (05/16).

As a Graduate (Tampa, 2020): Appeared in seven games...Scored two goals and added one assist...Totaled eight shots...Recovered six ground balls...Scored both goals against Saint Rose (03/07).

As a Senior: Appeared in 5 games during his senior season… Registered 2 goals, 2 points, 1 ground ball, and 3 caused turnovers… Had a goal against UMBC and Georgetown.

As a Junior: Appeared in 13 games… Registered six goals, two assists, eight points, four ground balls, and one caused turnover… Notched a season-high two points (1g, 1a) at Richmond… Had a pair of three-game goal-scoring streaks

As a Sophomore: Returned to Mount St Mary’s played in nine games during the season...Recorded one goal on the year against VMI...Had a caused turnover and a ground ball against Richmond

As a Freshman: Attended Mount St Mary’s… Sat out the 2016 season as a redshirt.

High School: Attended Northern Highlands Regional High School where he played for head coach Kyle Ojakian.
